Files:
- platform/cli/src/commands/status.ts (lines 196-205)

Context:
The current code at lines 196-205:
```typescript
const disabledBrowserTools = Array.isArray(data.disabledBrowserTools)
  ? (data.disabledBrowserTools as string[])
  : [];
if (disabledBrowserTools.length > 0) {
  console.log('');
  console.log(pc.bold('  Disabled Browser Tools'));
  for (const name of disabledBrowserTools) {
    console.log(`    ${pc.red(name)}`);
  }
}
```
This loops through 76 tool names. The important context is: browser tools are disabled when the extension is not connected (`data.extensionConnected === false`). When the extension IS connected, the tools are active and this list should be short or empty.

Changes:
Replace the `for` loop that prints each name with a single summary line:
```typescript
if (disabledBrowserTools.length > 0) {
  console.log('');
  const extensionConnected = data.extensionConnected === true;
  const reason = extensionConnected ? '' : ' — connect the Chrome extension to enable';
  console.log(pc.dim(`  ${disabledBrowserTools.length} browser tool${disabledBrowserTools.length === 1 ? '' : 's'} disabled${reason}`));
}
```

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the `--json` output path (line 126-128) — it should still include the full array
- The summary should only appear when `disabledBrowserTools.length > 0` (same condition as now)
- Keep the section position (after plugin details, before failed plugins)

